{"author":{"id":"11f56c2e7a2cb634892b4cf7e5d51bdc88cfe8b0eb217f0aae7f836b6d88fc66"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1566794742,"nonce":"B99w2H4eVIgsa8Cm+/8E/Ae7N0A=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU0ODUwNDAzNjM=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2545","origin":"github"},"title":"New Roary upgrade doesn't like spaces in filenames","message":"Within the new version of the Roary tool, the inputs are copied and renamed with `element_identifier` which is a good idea in itself. However, in most cases with Galaxy, if these gff inputs are outputs from another tool (such as Prokka) then `element_identifier` will contain spaces and perhaps other whitespace.\n\nExample:\nOriginal input file in Galaxy: `177: Prokka on data 61: gff`\nBecomes: `Prokka on data 61: gff.gff` which contains whitespace.\n\nIn the command block of `roary.xml`, the files to be analysed are added with `*.gff` which doesn't wrap them individually in `\"\"`...\n\nTherefore, roary cannot find the files as it splits them on whitespace... :(\n\n\n```\n\u003ccommand detect_errors=\"exit_code\"\u003e\u003c![CDATA[\n        \n        #for $gff in $gff_input.gffs\n          cp $gff '${gff.element_identifier}'.gff \u0026\u0026\n        #end for\n\n        roary\n          -f out\n          -p \\${GALAXY_SLOTS:-1}\n          -e\n          -n\n          -i '$percent_ident'\n          -cd '$core_diff'\n          -g '$advanced.maxclust'\n          $advanced.split_para\n          -t '$advanced.trans_tab'\n          -iv '$advanced.mcl'\n\n          *.gff\n          \n    ]]\u003e\u003c/command\u003e\n```","files":null}]}